title: Drawing, "Study for Duplicate of "Christiana"", March 1850
medium:
Graphite, White Chalk
Support: Gray Wove Paper
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at right margin: grey to the left/of ankle bone/ slight restraint/on the bone/shadow negative/grey tint/along the instep/ with viens/running across/obliquely with/....-/toes more red/especially toward/nails -greyish/tints at juncture/of toes with foot; at lower right: Study for foot of Matthew/in duplicate of Christiana/ March/50: on verso: DH
